1
00:00:08,333 --> 00:00:09,666
[SARU] Lunar Edomae,
a talented young singer,

2
00:00:09,750 --> 00:00:11,833
unexpectedly arrived at
Isono Eighth Junior High School,

3
00:00:11,916 --> 00:00:13,583
sparking a fierce
rivalry with the

4
00:00:13,666 --> 00:00:15,666
other popular
newcomer, Sun Seto.

5
00:00:15,750 --> 00:00:18,000
Now the school has divided
itself into warring factions,

6
00:00:18,083 --> 00:00:20,250
each supporting their
favorite of these two stars.

7
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:21,500
But who will win?

8
00:00:21,583 --> 00:00:24,250
These moron boys have
gone completely crazy!

9
00:00:28,291 --> 00:00:29,583
[NARRATOR]
Beneath the gently rolling

10
00:00:29,666 --> 00:00:31,791
waves of the Seto Inland Sea.

11
00:00:31,875 --> 00:00:35,458
Young Nagasumi's life is saved,
and forever changed.

12
00:00:35,541 --> 00:00:39,083
But as with any debt,
this one too must be repaid.

13
00:00:39,166 --> 00:00:41,000
So our story begins.

14
00:00:41,083 --> 00:00:45,541
Please humor them with a smile,
for young love is never easy.

15
00:00:48,166 --> 00:00:53,125
♪

16
00:02:33,083 --> 00:02:34,416
[LUNAR DUDE B] There he is!

17
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:36,750
[LUNAR DUDE A]
Nagasumi Michishio!

18
00:02:36,833 --> 00:02:38,541
[LUNAR DUDE B]
Don't let him get away!

19
00:02:41,125 --> 00:02:42,416
[LUNAR DUDE A] Nagasumi!

20
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:44,833
[LUNAR DUDE B] Come back
here, you dirty little rat!

21
00:02:44,916 --> 00:02:46,791
Why are you guys trying
to hunt me down, huh?

22
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:48,500
[LUNAR DUDE A] Because
Lunar likes you too much.

23
00:02:48,583 --> 00:02:49,916
You're in the way!

24
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,625
[LUNAR DUDE B] We'll kill you,
and then we can have all

25
00:02:51,708 --> 00:02:54,000
of precious Lunar's
love to ourselves!

26
00:02:54,083 --> 00:02:55,375
[NAGASUMI] Let me go!

27
00:02:56,291 --> 00:02:57,416
[LUNAR DUDE A]
Where did the rat go?

28
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:58,750
[LUNAR DUDE B] He won't escape!

29
00:02:58,833 --> 00:02:59,750
[NAGASUMI THINKS] I can't
believe people really

30
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:01,708
get this hooked on pop stars.

31
00:03:01,791 --> 00:03:03,041
[VOICES] You were, too.

32
00:03:03,125 --> 00:03:05,250
[SUN DUDE A] There he is!
Nagasumi's over there.

33
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:08,666
What, now Sun's fans
are after me too?

34
00:03:08,750 --> 00:03:11,083
[SUN DUDE A] Hey you, you'd
better stop right there, ya see.

35
00:03:11,166 --> 00:03:12,625
[SUN DUDE B] Just who
do you think you are?

36
00:03:12,708 --> 00:03:13,791
[SUN DUDE A] Ya see,
you're the one making it

37
00:03:13,875 --> 00:03:15,916
hard for us all to
put the moves on Sun.

38
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,333
[SUN DUDE B]
So we gotta get you, ya see.

39
00:03:17,416 --> 00:03:19,708
Leave me out of it! And what's
with the weird accents?

40
00:03:19,791 --> 00:03:21,791
[MAWARI]
You there! Stop it!

41
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:25,666
[SUN DUDE A] It's the
disciplinary committee, ya see!

42
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:28,000
What exactly do you
idiots think you're doing?

43
00:03:28,083 --> 00:03:30,625
Looks like you two are in
some serious need of discipline.

44
00:03:30,708 --> 00:03:31,958
[SUN DUDE A]
You can stay out of this.

45
00:03:32,041 --> 00:03:34,208
Don't you see Sun gives
us our reason for living?

46
00:03:34,291 --> 00:03:35,916
[SUN DUDE B]
Even wilting flowers bloom

47
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,500
in the light of
the beautiful Sun.

48
00:03:37,583 --> 00:03:40,000
[SUN DUDE A] She's our light!
Our light, don't ya see?

49
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:41,750
That, that's all nonsense!

50
00:03:41,833 --> 00:03:44,666
No, ya see!This is true love!

51
00:03:44,750 --> 00:03:47,083
You can make
your excuses later.

52
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,458
[NAGASUMI] I don't
understand what's

53
00:03:50,541 --> 00:03:51,666
going on at this school.

54
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:53,500
[CLASS REP] N-Nagasumi

55
00:03:53,958 --> 00:03:54,958
[NAGASUMI] Yes, Class Rep?

56
00:03:55,041 --> 00:03:56,875
Nagasumi, you need
to come this way.

57
00:03:56,958 --> 00:03:59,250
Um. What? Hey wait up,
I'm coming.

58
00:04:01,291 --> 00:04:02,958
[NAGASUMI] Whew!
Hey thanks a lot for

59
00:04:03,041 --> 00:04:04,291
saving my butt back there.

60
00:04:04,375 --> 00:04:05,708
[MAWARI] Shut up!

61
00:04:05,791 --> 00:04:07,458
[MAWARI] You can hang
onto your lousy thanks.

62
00:04:07,541 --> 00:04:09,833
Who do you think is
responsible for this situation?

63
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:11,333
[NAGASUMI] What,
are you saying it's me?

64
00:04:11,416 --> 00:04:14,000
I'm a member of the disciplinary
committee at this school.

65
00:04:14,083 --> 00:04:16,083
This isn't discipline.

66
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:17,750
[NAGASUMI] I can
see your point there.

67
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:20,291
[MAWARI] According to my
reliable intelligence network,

68
00:04:20,375 --> 00:04:22,166
this all started
because of a tug-of-war

69
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:23,833
between Lunar and Sun over you!

70
00:04:23,916 --> 00:04:25,458
[GIRL A] Nagasumi
you're a total sleaze ball.

71
00:04:25,541 --> 00:04:28,000
[GIRL B] You jerk!
[GIRL C] You womanizer!

72
00:04:28,083 --> 00:04:29,750
[NAGASUMI] Gossip
sure spreads quickly.

73
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:30,625
[MAWARI] Excuse me?

74
00:04:30,708 --> 00:04:31,750
No, what I
mean is your

75
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:33,125
intelligence network
is very impressive.

76
00:04:33,208 --> 00:04:35,791
Nagasumi, you really
are hopeless, aren't you? Well.

77
00:04:35,875 --> 00:04:36,333
[NAGASUMI] Huh?

78
00:04:36,416 --> 00:04:37,291
Which'll it be?

79
00:04:37,375 --> 00:04:38,333
[NAGASUMI] Which will what be?

80
00:04:38,416 --> 00:04:40,250
I'm asking you
to tell me which one

81
00:04:40,333 --> 00:04:42,125
of the girls you choose,
Sun or Lunar?

82
00:04:42,208 --> 00:04:43,333
[NAGASUMI] Um?

83
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:44,625
What does this situation
have to do with you?

84
00:04:45,291 --> 00:04:46,958
[MAWARI] This whole
thing is escalating because

85
00:04:47,041 --> 00:04:48,500
you won't take
a stand, you idiot.

86
00:04:48,583 --> 00:04:50,208
Crap. This isn't
going well at all.

87
00:04:50,291 --> 00:04:51,541
Help me!

88
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:53,083
[CLASS REP] Mawari,
I think you should calm down.

89
00:04:53,166 --> 00:04:55,333
[MAWARI] This is just one of
the reasons why all men suck!

90
00:04:55,416 --> 00:04:56,791
[GIRL 1] Nagasumi, you're slime.

91
00:04:56,875 --> 00:04:57,875
[GIRL 2] The scum of the earth.

92
00:04:57,958 --> 00:04:59,416
[GIRL 3] The enemy
of all womankind.

93
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:00,291
Let's get him.

94
00:05:00,375 --> 00:05:02,708
Why's this happening?

95
00:05:05,208 --> 00:05:07,791
[SUN] Come on, Lunar.
We should stop this, okay?

96
00:05:07,875 --> 00:05:10,291
But we can't. It's out
of our hands now.

97
00:05:10,375 --> 00:05:12,166
Sun, I don't want
to see harm come to

98
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:13,708
my fans any more than you do.

99
00:05:13,791 --> 00:05:16,208
But this battle can't possibly
end like this, you know.

100
00:05:16,291 --> 00:05:18,458
Not until I have victory!

101
00:05:18,541 --> 00:05:21,250
[LUNAR DUDES] Hail.
Lunar! Hail. Lunar! Hail!

102
00:05:21,333 --> 00:05:22,916
I still don't understand
why we had to

103
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,958
start a fight like
this in the first place.

104
00:05:25,041 --> 00:05:26,166
[Lunar laughs]

105
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:28,458
Because there's only
room for one heroine.

106
00:05:28,541 --> 00:05:30,333
[SUN] Okay. Let's just
say you're it then.

107
00:05:30,416 --> 00:05:32,333
[LUNAR] That pathetic,
laid-back attitude of yours

108
00:05:32,416 --> 00:05:34,458
really pisses me off,
you know that?

109
00:05:34,541 --> 00:05:36,291
Okay, Lunar.

110
00:05:39,708 --> 00:05:42,333
[Nagasumi cries out]

111
00:05:42,416 --> 00:05:44,500
They threw
me to the wolves!

112
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:45,750
[SUN DUDE A] It's Nagasumi!

113
00:05:45,833 --> 00:05:47,791
[SUN DUDE B] Let's make
him a sacrifice for Sun!

114
00:05:47,875 --> 00:05:49,125
[LUNAR DUDE A]
Don't let the rat escape!

115
00:05:49,208 --> 00:05:51,416
[LUNAR DUDE B] Hunt
Nagasumi down and kill him!

116
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:52,666
[Teacher A laughs]

117
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:54,375
It's good to see how
energetic the kids are.

118
00:05:54,458 --> 00:05:56,541
They've got a youthful
zeal to them these days.

119
00:05:56,625 --> 00:05:58,500
You know, I haven't
seen Mr. Seto in a while.

120
00:05:58,583 --> 00:05:59,791
Come to think of it,

121
00:05:59,875 --> 00:06:01,250
I haven't seen him or his
family in some time.

122
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:03,000
Teachers get
such freedom here.

123
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:05,875
So considerate
of them, isn't it?

124
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:09,750
[Nagasumi out of breath]

125
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:11,333
I finally gave
them the slip.

126
00:06:11,416 --> 00:06:13,291
That oughta teach
them to come after me.

127
00:06:13,375 --> 00:06:14,833
[SARU] Nagasumi Michishio!

128
00:06:14,916 --> 00:06:16,875
Aw come on just
leave me alone!

129
00:06:16,958 --> 00:06:19,791
[NAGASUMI] Wait,
I recognize that voice.

130
00:06:20,416 --> 00:06:21,750
[NAGASUMI] Chimp!

131
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:23,500
Wait, what are you doing
standing on a telephone pole?

132
00:06:23,583 --> 00:06:25,125
Listen well
to me, Nagasumi.

133
00:06:25,208 --> 00:06:27,958
Running away isn't going
to solve anything for you.

134
00:06:28,041 --> 00:06:30,041
Nothing at all, do you hear me?

135
00:06:30,125 --> 00:06:31,541
[NAGASUMI] What are you
talking about, monkey boy?

136
00:06:31,625 --> 00:06:34,166
Running away's obviously
my only choice right now!

137
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:36,000
[SARU] Now is the
time to face yourself.

138
00:06:36,083 --> 00:06:37,000
[NAGASUMI] Huh?

139
00:06:37,083 --> 00:06:38,583
You have to
overcome this, boy.

140
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:41,791
If you can't then you
will have no future.

141
00:06:42,583 --> 00:06:44,000
[NAGASUMI] Awakening!

142
00:06:44,083 --> 00:06:48,000
Chimp. Instruct me.
Tell me what should I do now?

143
00:06:48,083 --> 00:06:49,916
You must find the
path, Nagasumi.

144
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,375
Everyone is divided.

145
00:06:51,458 --> 00:06:52,833
You are the only one
who can intercede

146
00:06:52,916 --> 00:06:54,500
with both Lunar and Sun now.

147
00:06:54,583 --> 00:06:57,666
This school's last
hope resides in you!

148
00:06:59,416 --> 00:07:00,583
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
I understand now, Roshi.

149
00:07:00,666 --> 00:07:02,875
I have to find some way
to make peace with them.

150
00:07:02,958 --> 00:07:06,333
This fight is ridiculous.
It has to end.

151
00:07:06,416 --> 00:07:09,583
Go to them, Nagasumi.
Fight your hardest, Nagasumi.

152
00:07:09,666 --> 00:07:11,250
I can see it all clearly.

153
00:07:11,333 --> 00:07:13,166
Fulfill your destiny,
and you will become a

154
00:07:13,250 --> 00:07:16,291
great warrior who
will guide all your people.

155
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:19,583
[Nagasumi panting]

156
00:07:19,666 --> 00:07:20,958
[NAGASUMI] Sun!

157
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:26,375
[medical machines beeping]

158
00:07:26,458 --> 00:07:27,666
[NAGASUMI] Maki.

159
00:07:28,958 --> 00:07:30,000
[MOM] Nagasumi?

160
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:31,875
[NAGASUMI] Sun,
what happened to her?

161
00:07:35,208 --> 00:07:38,208
Maki was in a fight
with Lunar's bodyguards.

162
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:40,750
[REN] I'm sure she
fought well, but they

163
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:42,708
must have been too much for her.

164
00:07:44,041 --> 00:07:47,791
[REN] Apparently she thought Sun
would be worried so she hid.

165
00:07:48,291 --> 00:07:50,208
Sun just found her a while ago.

166
00:07:50,291 --> 00:07:54,000
Oh Miss Sun. I'm
so sorry, so sorry.

167
00:07:54,083 --> 00:07:55,291
Maki.

168
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:58,750
[REN] She's been talkin'
in her sleep for a while.

169
00:07:59,125 --> 00:08:01,958
[GOZABURO] We just finished
treatin' her not long ago.

170
00:08:02,041 --> 00:08:04,250
[GOZABURO] Those
wounds are serious.

171
00:08:05,125 --> 00:08:06,250
[GOZABURO] Hey Maki.

172
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:07,625
Don't you think it's
about time we taught

173
00:08:07,708 --> 00:08:09,500
those damn Edomae
a thing or two

174
00:08:09,583 --> 00:08:11,875
about how we yakuza
settle our scores?

175
00:08:13,666 --> 00:08:15,375
[GOZABURO]
We're hittin' the mattresses.

176
00:08:15,458 --> 00:08:17,250
[NAGASUMI AND MOM]
You're kidding!

177
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:20,083
I won't forgive them if they
come crawling to beg for it.

178
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:21,166
Nothin' can stop me now!

179
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:22,708
Nagasumi, I must
ask you and your mother,

180
00:08:22,791 --> 00:08:26,416
to stay away from this battle.
I do hope you understand.

181
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:29,000
[MASA] This isn't as simple as a
fight between Lunar and Maki.

182
00:08:29,083 --> 00:08:30,625
A Seto member was taken down

183
00:08:30,708 --> 00:08:32,583
by a member of
the Edomae family.

184
00:08:32,666 --> 00:08:35,750
It's best settled between
just our two families.

185
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:37,083
Really Ren?

186
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:38,291
We'll do our
best to avoid

187
00:08:38,375 --> 00:08:40,083
causin' ya any
trouble with this.

188
00:08:40,166 --> 00:08:42,041
Please go about
your normal lives.

189
00:08:42,125 --> 00:08:43,375
But we--

190
00:08:46,208 --> 00:08:49,041
[SUN] Right now I'm gonna go
and take care of Lunar myself.

191
00:08:49,125 --> 00:08:52,083
No, hold on Sun. We
don't need more violence!

192
00:08:52,166 --> 00:08:53,458
I hate violence, too.

193
00:08:53,541 --> 00:08:55,250
You know this isn't what
I wanted to happen.

194
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:56,958
But a good friend of
the family's been hurt,

195
00:08:57,041 --> 00:08:59,041
and I'm not gonna
take that quietly, so--

196
00:08:59,125 --> 00:09:01,083
[NAGASUMI] Aren't
I your husband, Sun?

197
00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:03,333
Doesn't that make me a
part of the Seto gang too?

198
00:09:03,416 --> 00:09:05,083
I can't just let
my entire family

199
00:09:05,166 --> 00:09:07,166
be put in danger like this.

200
00:09:09,083 --> 00:09:10,500
[GOZABURO] Did ya call
yerself her husband, maggot?

201
00:09:10,583 --> 00:09:13,583
I know you're right
about this, Nagasumi.

202
00:09:13,666 --> 00:09:14,750
But what now?

203
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:17,958
What else can I possibly
do to stop Lunar?

204
00:09:19,166 --> 00:09:21,958
[rolling thunder in
the distance]

205
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,000
[NAGASUMI] This is
a message from Sun.

206
00:09:26,083 --> 00:09:27,500
We'll fight this with songs.

207
00:09:27,583 --> 00:09:30,250
Oh, what an amusing
plan Sun thought up.

208
00:09:30,333 --> 00:09:32,916
Well all right then... of
course if we win the fight.

209
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,291
We trust you'll
agree to become our

210
00:09:34,375 --> 00:09:37,166
manservant and leave
Sun once and for all.

211
00:09:37,250 --> 00:09:39,375
And, and if you
lose, what then?

212
00:09:40,375 --> 00:09:41,541
Oh come on.

213
00:09:41,625 --> 00:09:44,333
As if we could possibly
lose to that silly girl.

214
00:09:49,125 --> 00:09:52,750
[SARU] The big storm,
of angry, raging battle.

215
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,416
It comes.

216
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:57,291
The battle of the
great age of gods...

217
00:09:57,375 --> 00:09:59,750
Begins now!

218
00:10:10,541 --> 00:10:13,458
[LUNAR THINKS] A mermaid's voice
is her pride and her weapon.

219
00:10:13,541 --> 00:10:17,541
Our singing is everything
to us. We can't lose.

220
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:21,708
Lunar it's packed!
The house is just packed!

221
00:10:22,291 --> 00:10:24,375
[KAMATA] Really, I didn't know
what had gotten into you.

222
00:10:24,458 --> 00:10:26,250
First you skip work for days.

223
00:10:26,333 --> 00:10:28,166
And then you,
the darling celebrity

224
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:30,000
of the entire nation,
ask to do a surprise

225
00:10:30,083 --> 00:10:32,250
concert in some little
junior high school?

226
00:10:32,333 --> 00:10:33,791
As soon as I announced
it yesterday,

227
00:10:33,875 --> 00:10:35,208
I was drowned in phone calls

228
00:10:35,291 --> 00:10:37,583
from the talk shows
and the news.

229
00:10:37,666 --> 00:10:39,041
[LUNAR] The stage is set.

230
00:10:39,125 --> 00:10:41,333
We've waited so
long for this day.

231
00:10:41,416 --> 00:10:42,958
And the wait has
been a painful one,

232
00:10:43,041 --> 00:10:44,916
but it's here at last.

233
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:45,916
Here and now.

234
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,875
We'll finally take
Sun Seto down.

235
00:10:47,958 --> 00:10:49,625
We've spent years
of mortification,

236
00:10:49,708 --> 00:10:51,750
of humiliation, of deep shame.

